§ 2. RIGHTS GRANTED

Subject to the conditions set forth in this License, the Neuro Project
Contributors hereby grant you the following rights:

  2.1  PERSONAL USE: You may use, study, run, and modify the Software for
       Personal Use (§ 1.7) without restriction beyond the conditions of
       this License.

  2.2  CONTRIBUTION: You may modify the Software and submit modifications as
       contributions to the official project repository, subject to § 10.

  2.3  NON-COMMERCIAL DISTRIBUTION: You may distribute the Software or
       Derivative Works to third parties for non-commercial purposes, provided
       you satisfy all conditions of Part IV (Conditions).

  2.4  INTERNAL BUSINESS USE: Organizations may use the Software for Internal
       Business Use (§ 1.8) without a separate commercial license, provided
       they satisfy the attribution conditions of § 5.1 in any internal
       materials that reference the Software.

  2.5  COMMERCIAL DISTRIBUTION: You may distribute the Software or Derivative
       Works as part of Commercial Distribution (§ 1.9) provided that you
       satisfy all conditions of Part IV (Conditions), AND either:

         (a) Obtain a separate written Commercial Distribution License from
             the Neuro Project; or

         (b) Your commercial distribution is of a Derivative Work that
             constitutes a genuine independent fork under a distinct name
             per § 6, is fully source-available under this License, and
             does not engage in Competitive AI Reproduction or unauthorized
             use of Non-Public Proprietary Elements.

  No rights are granted beyond those explicitly stated in this § 2.

